2026-06-15 03:11:25,803 DEBUG response: **Decision:** Yes, it’s worth tweeting. The commits track a clear problem-solution arc: replacing static, fragile portfolio code with a dynamic routing structure, while actually fixing mobile responsiveness instead of layering on CSS filter patches. It’s unglamorous, but the maintenance pain is genuinely relatable for anyone who’s built their own site.

**Tweet options:**

1. Hardcoding my projects page worked until it didn’t. Switched to a dynamic routing setup so I can just update one data file and have the grid wire itself up.

2. Tested my site on anything smaller than a laptop screen and immediately regretted it. Replaced CSS filter patches with proper responsive breakpoints and rebuilt the project section to render from data instead of static components.

3. Frontend is just stubbornness with margins and brightness values. Finally stopped touching the main layout file every time I wanted to add a project, and set up a clean route/data structure. Much less bleeding.
